  <title>How do I Edit, Save, and Move my Styling?</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Styling<keyword>Settings</keyword><keyword>Style</keyword><keyword>Theme</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">... edit, save, and move my Styling</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">How to edit your Settings, Styles and Theme.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">We call the<text styleclass="VariableName"> Style</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Theme, </text><text styleclass="Body Text">and</text> <text styleclass="VariableName">Settings</text> the <text styleclass="VariableName">Styling</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">Each time you exit </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, we save for you the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Styling</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> to </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.INI</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> and </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.XML.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> uses the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Styling</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> automatically the next time it starts. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="VariableName">Styling Definitions:</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="3" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:106px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Theme : </para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:599px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Border, Icon, and dialog colors. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">Use <text styleclass="VariableName">Application Settings : General tab &gt; </text><text styleclass="Separator">Theme Settings </text><text styleclass="VariableName"> &gt; Target Theme</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">Select one of these <text styleclass="VariableName">Themes</text>: </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Windows, Charcoal Dark Slate, Aqua Light Slate, Windows10 Dark, Tablet Dark, Slate Classico, Windows10 Slate Gray, Windows 10.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Note, this help uses Charcoal Dark Slate.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:106px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Style : </para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:599px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Load a Style</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Click the <link displaytype="button" type="topiclink" href="">Load<title>Load button</title></link><text styleclass="VariableName"> </text>button to open a Style</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName">Dark.XML</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> - is intended to be used with dark themes, for example, Charcoal Dark Slate. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName">Light.XML</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> - is intended to be used with light theme, for example, Aqua Light Slate.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Save a Style</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Click the <link displaytype="button" type="topiclink" href="">Save<title>Save button</title></link><text styleclass="VariableName"> </text>button<text styleclass="VariableName">:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Save any changes you have made to Style file-name</para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text style="color:#ff0000;">Do NOT overwrite Dark.XML or Light.XML.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:106px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Application Settings : </para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:599px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal">Edit icon-sizes, number-formats and colors for different elements<text styleclass="Body Text">:</text></para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="VariableName-indent" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="VariableName-indent">Application-Settings &gt; Graphics tab &gt; <text styleclass="Separator">Display Colors</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">There are many other settings you can make to suit your preferences. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Note: You can also save and load these with the Save and Load buttons</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><anchor id="SaveStyle"><keywords><keyword>Save the Style</keyword></keywords></anchor>Save the Styling</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You may want to save your personal styling, especially if different people use <text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner</text> on the same PC.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:'Segoe UI Semibold'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="T_Menu">File menu &gt; Application-Settings</text> <text styleclass="VariableName">: </text></li>
            <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">Click the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Save</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> button at the bottom of the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Application-Settings dialog</text><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text">The default path for your Styling should open </text><text styleclass="VariableName">&lt;CommonAppData&gt;\PSMotion\Style \ Comma\</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> or </text><text styleclass="VariableName">\Stop\</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You see <text styleclass="VariableName">Dark.XML</text> and <text styleclass="VariableName">Light.XML</text> files (and others).</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">DO NOT OVERWRITE</text><text styleclass="Normal"> </text>these files<text styleclass="Normal">.</text></para>
          <list id="2" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Save the Styling to <text styleclass="VariableName">...style\Comma\My-style-name.XML</text> if your number system uses a comma <text styleclass="VariableName">&apos;,&apos; </text>as the decimal symbol.</li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Save the Styling to <text styleclass="VariableName">...style\Stop\ My-style-name.XML </text>if your number system uses a stop<text styleclass="VariableName"> &apos;.&apos;</text> as the decimal symbol.</li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Move your Styling</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You may want to move your styling to a different computer for your own use, or to distribute the Styling to all Workstations.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <list id="3" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:'Segoe UI Semibold'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="B Bullets">Save the active <text styleclass="VariableName">Styling</text> to a <text styleclass="VariableName-IT">My-file-name.XML</text> - see <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="" anchor="SaveStyle">preceding section</link>.<text styleclass="VariableName"> </text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> Remember, <text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">DO NOT OVERWRITE</text><text styleclass="Normal"> the default </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Dark.XML </text><text styleclass="Normal">and </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Light.XML</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> files.</text></para>
          <list id="3" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:'Segoe UI Semibold'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="Bullets">Exit </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner </text></li>
            <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Use File-Explorer to navigate to:</text></li>
          </list>
          <list id="4" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName">&lt;CommonAppData&gt;\PSMotion\style\Comma</text> <text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">if your number system uses a comma </text>&apos;,&apos; <text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">as the decimal symbol.</text></li>
          </list>
          <list id="5" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName">&lt;CommonAppData&gt;\PSMotion\style\Stop</text> <text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">if your number system uses a stop </text>&apos;.&apos; <text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">as the decimal symbol.</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Notes">Note 1</text>: <text styleclass="VariableName">&lt;CommonAppData&gt;</text> is usually <text styleclass="VariableName">C:\ProgramData\</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName">Note 2: </text>If you cannot see <text styleclass="VariableName">C:\ProgramData\ .</text>.. then i<text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">n </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Windows File Explorer:</text></para>
          <list id="6" type="ol" listtype="lower-alpha" formatstring="%0:s)" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-family:'Segoe UI Semibold'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Click <text styleclass="VariableName">View</text> tab<text styleclass="VariableName"> </text></li>
            <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Click <text styleclass="VariableName">Hidden Items</text> check-box in the <text styleclass="VariableName">Show/hide</text> group-box. </li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;"/></para>
          <list id="7" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="4" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:'Segoe UI Semibold'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets">Copy <text styleclass="VariableName">My-style-name.XML</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">, </text><text styleclass="Body Text">to a </text><text styleclass="VariableName">USB</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> stick, for example</text><text styleclass="VariableName">. </text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You also need to make copies of the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.INI</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> and </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.XML</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> files</text></para>
          <list id="8" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="5" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:'Segoe UI Semibold'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets">Use File-Explorer to navigate to path:<text styleclass="VariableName"> </text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">&lt;LocalAppData&gt; C:\users\</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="background-color:#ffff00;">&lt;user-name&gt;</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">\AppData\Local\PSMotion\IniFiles</text><text styleclass="VariableName">\</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets">Copy <text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.INI</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT"> </text><text styleclass="Body Text">and</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT"> </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.XML </text><text styleclass="Body Text">to a </text><text styleclass="VariableName">USB</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> stick</text><text styleclass="VariableName">. </text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">On the other Workstation:</para>
          <list id="8" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="5" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:'Segoe UI Semibold'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="HowTo NO STEP">Replace the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.INI</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT"> </text><text styleclass="Body Text">and</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT"> </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner.XML</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> files on the workstation, with the files on your </text><text styleclass="VariableName">USB</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> stick</text><text styleclass="VariableName"> </text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="HowTo NO STEP">Copy </text><text styleclass="VariableName">My-style-name.XML</text><text styleclass="HowTo NO STEP"> from your stick into the path used for styling - </text><text styleclass="Body Text">see </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="" anchor="SaveStyle" styleclass="Body Text">preceding sections</link><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text">Start</text><text styleclass="HowTo NO STEP"> </text><text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> on the </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">workstation</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Click </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Application-Settings &gt; Load button</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="HowTo STEPNotPink" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">Load </text><text styleclass="VariableName">My-style-name.XML</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> from the USB stick as the new style.</text><text styleclass="VariableName"> </text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text">Click</text><text styleclass="VariableName"> Save</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> button</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Save the <text styleclass="VariableName">Styling</text> to <text styleclass="VariableName">&lt;CommonAppData&gt;</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> is usually </text><text styleclass="VariableName">C:\ProgramData\</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">The <text styleclass="VariableName">Theme, Style</text> and <text styleclass="VariableName">Application-Settings</text> are saved automatically as defaults. They load the next time you start <text styleclass="VariableName">MechDesigner</text>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
